1.title: Ariel Chobaz
1.plot: This week is the premiere of Pensado's Place with mixing engineer Dave Pensado, his manager Herb Trawick, and engineer Zan Nakari. They are joined in studio by mixing engineer Ariel Chobaz who recently worked with Nicki Minaj on her album. In this week's Into The Lair, Dave Pensado goes over some of his favorite new compressor and eq plug-ins that he uses on his mixes. They also break down the tracks for Linkin Park's 'Waiting for the End' in this week's Playback, and the group takes questions from viewers during Corner Office.

2.title: Jean-Marie
2.plot: In 2nd episode of Pensado's Place with mixing engineer Dave Pensado, Herb Trawick, and Zan Nakari are joined by world renowned mixing engineer Jean-Marie Horvat (Michael Jackson, Justin Timberlake, TI, Reba Mcentire, Beyonce, etc.). On this week's Into The Lair, Dave goes over stereo buss compression and the difference between compressors and limiters.

3.title: Dylan '3D' Dresdow
3.plot: In the 3rd episode of Pensado's Place, Dave Pensado is joined by GRAMMY award winning mixer Dylan "3D" Dresdow. (Michael Jackson, Black Eyed Peas, Mariah Carey, Rihanna, Usher, The Game, Nas, Ciara, Talib Kweli, Macy Gray, Bone Thugs & Harmony, Herbie Hancock, Chris Brown, Ricky Martin and many more). On this week's Into The Lair, Dave goes talks about how he Busses tracks for mixing, and the various plug-ins he uses on those busses. The crew breaks down PitBull's newest single featuring T-Pain, "Hey Baby (drop it to the floor)".

4.title: Tony Maserati
4.plot: In the 4th episode of Pensado's Place, Dave Pensado is joined by legendary engineer and mixer Tony Maserati (Marc Anthony, James Brown, Mariah Carey, Destiny's Child, R. Kelly, Jennifer Lopez, Ricky Martin, Mya, Notorious B.I.G., Puff Daddy, Jessica Simpson, Tupac, Jason Mraz etc.). This week's episode was devoted entirely to the passionate discussion between Dave and Tony regarding all things mixing and engineering. New plug-ins such as the Slate Digital FG-X and the Waves C6 were covered, as well as various mixing concepts, how Will.i.am is the poster child for the ...

5.title: Audio Production Q&A with Dave Pensado
5.plot: In the 5th episode of Pensado's Place, Dave hosts an all Q&A episode with tons of great viewer questions! With Part 2/2 of the latest "Into The Lair", Dave takes you through some tools he used on the mix for "Shorty is a Weirdo" by Mr. Midwest and Ray J. Get a behind the scene look at how your favorite songs were mixed and the tools that were used by Dave!

6.title: Manny Marroquin
6.plot: In the 7th Episode of Pensado's Place, Dave is joined by Colin McDowell of McDSP PlugIns to give a special offer to all Pensado's Place viewers! In this week's Into The Lair, Dave talks about all things vocals including his favorite effects.

7.title: Colin McDowell
7.plot: In the 7th Episode of Pensado's Place, Dave is joined by Colin McDowell of McDSP PlugIns to give a special offer to all Pensado's Place viewers! In this week's Into The Lair, Dave talks about all things vocals including his favorite effects.

8.title: Jaycen Joshua
8.plot: In the 8th Episode of Pensado's Place, Dave is joined by GRAMMY award winning mixer Jaycen Joshua! This week's Into The Lair, dave interviews GRAMMY nominated engineers Andrew Wuepper and Brian "B-Love" Thomas about their vocal tracking methods.

9.title: Maureen Droney
9.plot: In the 9th Episode of Pensado's Place, Maureen Droney, Sr. Executive Director of the Producers & Engineers Wing of the Recording Academy joins Dave, Herb, and Zan to discuss the GRAMMY's and other aspects of NARAS (National Academy of Recording Arts and Sciences).

10.title: James Murray
10.plot: In the 10th episode of Pensado's Place, Larabee Studio's assistant engineers (Chris Galland, Drew Adams, and Jesus Garnica) join Dave to discuss how they became assistants and their day-to-day work. This week's ITL is part 1 of 2 of an in-depth walk-through of how Dave uses vocal reverbs and effects! In this week's Corner Office, Dave and the gang are answering the top 3 "Liked" questions via our facebook fanpage, and Producer James Murray (Alien Ant Farm, Drowning Pool, etc) joins Dave to talk about the gear he uses in The Batters Box!

11.title: Emanuel 'E-Man' Kiriakou
11.plot: In the 11th episode of Pensado's Place, Dave's guest is Producer Emanuel ""E-Man"" Kiriakou (Whitney Houston, Jordin Sparks, Selena Gomez, etc). This week's ITL is a continuation of last week's that talks all about vocal effects and various techniques.

12.title: Dann and David Huff
12.plot: In the 12th episode of Pensado's Place, Dann and David Huff join dave from Nashville via Skype to discuss Rascal Flatts, Keither Urban, and all things engineering and production! This week's ITL discusses clearing elements out of the middle to make room for vocals, as well as tricks to widen your mixes.

13.title: Ed Cherney
13.plot: In the 13th episode of Pensado's Place, engineering legend (and GRAMMY and TEC award winner) Ed Cherney stops by to chat with Dave and answer viewer questions in the ""Corner Office"". Dave and Ed then talk about their favorite gear in ""The Batters Box"", and another great ""Into The Lair"" which includes 4 distinct methods for getting instruments to sit better in the mix, as well as get more width and depth to your mixes by clearing things out of the middle!

14.title: Mike Dean
14.plot: In the 14th episode of Pensado's Place, Kanye West's engineer Mike Dean joins Dave and Herb to talk about his career, pioneering the "Dirty South" sound, and working with Kanye west on all of his albums! Dave and Mike then take viewer questions from the chatroom and facebook in "The Corner Office", followed by this week's "Batter's Box", where Mike answers Dave's rapid-fire questions regarding the gear he uses. This week's "Into The Lair" is at the end of the show, and is a continuation from last week's where Dave gives four distinct examples of how to clear out the ...

15.title: Bruce Swedien
15.plot: In the 15th episode of Pensado's Place, Engineering legend Bruce Swedien joins Dave, Herb, and Drew from his private studio in central Florida to discuss his career, engineering philosophy, and answer viewers questions. The entire episode is devoted to Bruce as he takes us on a tour of his private studio, shows us his recording set ups, and shares his engineering philosophies.

16.title: Mark Loughman
16.plot: In the 16th episode of Pensado's Place starts off with an in-depth look into the world of high-end mic pre's with BAE Audio's own Mark Loughman. They discuss the history of the venerable 1073 mic pre, and how Mark has managed to not only recreate, but improve upon this industry classic. Our guest is 3-time GRAMMY award winning mixer Phil Tan (Rihanna, Wiz Khalifa, Snoop Dogg, Enrique Iglesias, Fergie, Usher, Mariah Carey). He joins Dave and the gang via Skype to talk about his career, techniques, and favorite gear.

17.title: Joe Baressi
17.plot: In the 17th Episode of Pensado's Place, Joe Baressi, One of the best Rock Engineer, Producer, and Mixers, joins Dave in studio to talk about his career and methodology. The episode kicks off with a follow up to Episode #16's ""Into The Lair"", featuring the amazing Esthero singing through the fantastic BAE mic preamps at Larrabee studios!

18.title: Michael Brauer
18.plot: In the 18th episode of Penado's Place, 4-time GRAMMY winning Mixing Engineer Michael Brauer joins Dave via Skype to give a tour of his studio and outboard gear, as well as talk about his infamous ""Brauerize®"" compression technique in detail!

19.title: All Q+A
19.plot: In this week's episode of Pensado's Place, Dave and Herb host one of Dave's past assistants, engineer Andrew Wuepper! Andrew has worked with such artists as Katy Perry, Usher, and mixed Frank Ocean's latest hit "Novacane". Dave and Andrew discuss engineering and mixing techniques that Andrew has used on his latest work, and take live viewer questions in "The Corner Office". Andrew dishes on his favorite plug-ins and hardware in "The Batter's Box", and in this week's "Into The Lair", Dave explains some of his compression techniques in the box!

22.title: Jack Joseph Puig
22.plot: Dave Pensado is proud to welcome the multiple GRAMMY award winning mixer, producer, and friend - Jack Joseph Puig. To quote Steve Kurutz from AllMusic.com, Jack Joseph Puig is "Known for his ability to merge the sounds of the past three decades to create something that is thoroughly modern...". Jack has worked with artists such as Goo Goo Dolls, The Black Crowes, John Mayer, Weezer, Fiona Apple, Green Day, The Counting Crows, No Doubt, Klaxons, Panic at the Disco, Stone Temple Pilots, U2, and many others.

23.title: Tricky Steward

"Elliott has produced numerous albums and hit singles for various music artists including his mother, Dionne Warwick, as well as Destiny's Child, Beyonce, P!nk, Gwen Stefani, Jessica Simpson, Christina Aguilera, Mýa, and Macy Gray. Damon's production has earned him a Grammy and seven Grammy nominations."

66.title: Ross Hogarth
66.plot: In the 66th episode of Pensado's Place, Dave and Herb are joined by 2-Time GRAMMY Award winning Engineer/Mixer/Produce Ross Hogarth! Ross has worked with such artists as Van Halen, Roger Waters, The Black Crowes, Shawn Colvin, John Mellencamp, R.E.M. and many, many more!

68.title: Brian "B-Luv" Thomas
68.plot: Recording engineer Brian "B-Luv" Thomas joins Dave and Herb on the 68th episode of Pensado's Place. Brian is has tracked some of the biggest artists of the last decade including Katy Perry, Christina Aguilera, Future, The-Dream, as well as newer acts such as The Wanted and Karmin and many etc.

69.title: Steve Slate
69.plot: Steven Slate (Producer, Engineer, and CEO of Slate Digital and Slate Pro Audio) joins Dave and Herb on the 69th episode of Pensado's Place! Steven is behind the must-have drum samples for top producers and engineers as well as the creator of innovative drum replacement software, analog emulation plugins, and now analog outboard gear. See the passion behind the awesome products and sound in this episode of Pensado's Place!

70.title: Michael Brauer
70.plot: Mixing Engineer Michael Brauer joins Dave and Herb on the 70th episode of Pensado's Place! Skyping in from Electric Lady Studios, NY, Michael talks about his methodology when transitioning from mixing one genre to a drastically different one, along with his approach to starting a mix for a band and what to focus on. Later on Michael joins Dave in the Batter's Box and answer's viewer's questions in this week's Corner Office.

82.plot: Neff-U talks about how important God is in his creative process, and how performing music in church helped set the foundation for working with today's top artists.

83.title: Tom Elmhirst
83.plot: Dave and Herb are joined by GRAMMY Award-winning mix engineer Tom Elmhirst! (Adele, Amy Winehouse, Mark Ronson, Hot Chip).

84.title: Ward Hake
84.plot: The trio talk about how Ward started out as a musician, songwriter, and producer, and how he carried those skill sets into his current role supervising all of the music for hit shows as Glee, Modern Family, The Simpsons, Family Guy, How I Met Your Mother, 24, and many more.

85.title: Mike Shipley
85.plot: In the 85th episode of Pensado's Place, Dave and Herb are joined by mix master Mike Shipley! Mike was in the studio or behind the board for some of the greatest albums from acts like Queen, Keith Urban, AC/DC, Def Leppard, Van Halen, Aerosmith, Tom Petty, Tim McGraw, Maroon 5, Faith Hill, Nickelback, Green Day, The Black Crowes, Alison Krauss, Papa Roach, My Chemical Romance.

91.title: Dave Pensado
91.plot: In the 91st episode of Pensado's Place, the tables turn as Jack Joseph Puig interviews Dave Pensado from the House of Rock in Santa Monica, CA in this special 2-part, exclusive interview! In part 1, JJP asks Dave about his past as a musician playing in bands, how he became an engineer, his work with Ron Fair and A-List artists, and much, much more!

92.title: Dave Pensado
92.plot: Part 2 of Jack Joseph Puig interviewing Dave Pensado from the House of Rock in Santa Monica, CA in this special 2-part, exclusive interview! In part 2, Dave gets put in the Batter's Box and answer's JJP's questions having to do with how Dave lays out sessions on the console, what kind of level he sends to mastering engineers, and the experience of working with some of the top artists of the last 30 years.

93.title: Greg Wells
93.plot: Producer Greg Wells returns to join Dave and Herb discuss working with Katy Perry, All American Rejects, Recording Horns, Drums, and much more on the 93rd episode of Pensado's Place! In this week's ITL, Greg and Engineer Ian MacGregor go over their drum tracking process from Greg Wells' studio.

94.title: Raphael Saadiq
94.plot: Singer, songwriter, musician, guitarist, bassist and record producer Raphael Saadiq joins Dave and Herb on the 94th episode of Pensado's Place! Dave asks Raphael about his days in Tony! Toni! Toné!, his work with Prince, his recording and album making method, his exploration into music for TV, Film, and Theater. In this week's Into The Lair, Dave discusses some ear training techniques in Part 1 of a 2-part ITL on the subject.

95.title: Anthony Kilhoffer
95.plot: 3 time GRAMMY-award winning Producer and Mix Engineer Anthony Kilhoffer joins Dave and Herb on the 95th episode of Pensado's Place! The trio talk about his work on Kanye West's My Beautiful Dark Twisted Fantasy as well as Kid Cudi's Man on the Moon II. In this week's Into The Lair, Dave discusses some ear training techniques in Part 2 of a 2-part ITL on the subject.

96.title: Charlie Wilson
96.plot: Charlie Wilson, Musical Director for Rihanna and Justin Timberlake, joins Dave and Herb on the 96th episode of Pensado's Place! The trio discuss Charlie's path to, and working as, a musical director for today's top acts. In this week's Into The Lair, Dave discusses dealing with Low-End in a mix, and provides some detailed examples of his mixing process.

97.title: Derek Ali
97.plot: Mixed By Ali (Derek Ali), Mix Engineer for Kendrick Lamar's Good Kid, M.A.A.D City, joins Dave and Herb on the 97th episode of Pensado's Place! The trio discuss Derek's work on Kendrick's breakout album, as well as working with Doctor Dre, and his own mixing process. In this week's Into The Lair, Dave shows off some vocal mixing techniques he used on a recent Earth Wind & Fire track.

98.title: Joe Barresi
98.plot: Joe Barresi (Tool, Queens of the Stone Age, Coheed and Cambria, Bad Religion, Soundgarden) joins Dave and Herb on the 98th episode of Pensado's Place! The trio discuss how Joe gets a some of the best drum and guitar sounds in the business, as well as working with Soundgarden on their latest release, "King Animal". In this week's Into The Lair, Dave shows how to use delays without plug-ins or hardware!

99.title: Leslie Ann Jones
99.plot: GRAMMY Award-Winning Engineer Leslie Ann Jones (Herbie Hancock, Santana, and countless film scores) sits down with Dave Pensado for a special interview at Skywalker Ranch in Marin County, CA. Leslie talks about her percussionist and band leader father, Spike Jones, her path to becoming a GRAMMY-winning recording Engineer, her work at Skywalker Ranch, and her views on how to increase the role of women in the audio industry. Leslie also takes Dave out ont he scoring stage, and explains some of the technological intricacies of the facilities there.

1.title: Pete Lyman
1.plot: Pete Lyman, Mastering Engineer and co-owner of Infrasonic Sound (http://infrasonicsound.com/) joins Dave and Herb on the 100th episode of Pensado's Place! The trio talk about the resurgence of vinyl (including what you need to know if you want to have your mix mastered for vinyl), answer common mastering questions, and talk about Pete's process when mastering. This week's "Into The Lair" covers mixing background vocals!

3.title: Greg Wells: Pensado's Place NAMM 2013 Special
3.plot: Producer Greg Wells joins Dave Pensado and Herb Trawick on stage at the Avid booth at NAMM 2013

4.title: Michael Fitzpatrick: Pensado's Place NAMM 2013 Special
4.plot: Michael Fitzpatrick of Fitz and The Tantrums joins Dave Pensado and Herb Trawick on stage at the Avid booth at NAMM 2013

101.title: Chris Baseford
101.plot: Chris Baseford, engineer for the likes of Rob Zombie, Tommy Lee/Motley Crue, Fuel joins Dave and Herb on the 101st episode of Pensado's Place! Chris reveals some of his favorite techniques for recording a great rock guitar sound, as well as Chris' work re-constructing mixes of classic tracks for the Rock Band and Guitar Hero franchises.

103.title: Printz Board
103.plot: Musician, producer, songwriter and musical director for The Black Eyed Peas, Printz Board joins Dave and Herb on the 103rd episode of Pensado's Place! The three talk about Printz' work with will.i.am and BEP, including the story of how they wrote "Where Is The Love? one night before leaving to go out. Printz talks about MDing and what goes on while touring with The Black Eyed peas, as well as answers viewers questions in this weeks "Corner Office"!

104.title: Ron Fair
104.plot: Chief Creative Officer / EVP of Virgin Records, Ron Fair sits down with Dave and Herb on the 104th episode of Pensado's Place! The three talk about the current state of the music business, how labels are evolving, his role at virgin records, and advice for those looking to get into the music industry. This is an incredible episode you don't want to miss!

105.title: Manny Marroquin
105.plot: 5 time GRAMMY award winning mix engineer, Manny Marroquin sits down with Dave and Herb on the 105th episode of Pensado's Place! The three talk about Manny's work on the new Imagine Dragon's record (produced by past guest, Alex Da Kid) the latest Bruno Mars album, Linkin Park, Alicia Keys and more! You don't want to miss these two legends talking shop!

106.title: Tony Hoffer
106.plot: Producer and Mix Engineer Tony Hoffer (Beck, M83, Silversun Pickups, Depeche Mode) sits down with Dave and Herb on the 106th episode of Pensado's Place! Dave and Tony discuss Tony's recent work on M83's "Midnight City", Silversun Pickups's "Carnavas", as well as his philosophies and methods when it comes to his mix and production work.

107.title: Jacob Luttrell
107.plot: The man behind such hits as "Tonight (I'm Lovin' You.)" recorded by Enrique Iglesias and "Wild Ones," recorded by Flo Rida & Sia Furler - Songwriter Jacob Luttrell sits down with Dave and Herb to talk shop.

108.title: Neal Avron
108.plot: Producer and Mix Engineer Neal Avron (Everclear, Switchfoot, New Found Glory, Fall Out Boy, Yellowcard, Weezer, Sara Bareilles, Anberlin) sits down with Dave and Herb to talk shop.

109.title: Cat Gray and Brian Teed
109.plot: Musical Director for the TV Show "Let's Make A Deal", Cat Gray and his colleague Brian Teed take us through a day of production on the hit TV show "Let's Make a Deal".

110.title: François Tétaz
110.plot: Producer and Mix Engineer François Tétaz (Gotya, Kimbra) sits down with Dave and Herb to talk shop.

111.title: Danja

112.title: Showtek

113.title: Sean 'Sully' Sullivan
113.plot: Dave and Herb are joined by Sean "Sully" Sullivan, Engineer and FOH Mix Engineer for acts such as Beck, Rihanna, Thom Yorke, Beastie Boys, Sheryl Crow, Norah Jones (and many more).

114.title: Rodney 'Darkchild' Jerkins
114.plot: Songwriter, producer, and musician Rodney Jerkins (Jennifer Lopez, Michael Jackson, Justin Bieber, Whitney Houston and Britney Spears just to name a few) joins Dave and Herb to talk shop.

115.title: Mick Guzauski
115.plot: Mix Engineer Mick Guzauski (Earth, Wind and Fire, Eric Clapton, Mariah Carey, Baby Face, Boyz to Men, Daft Punk) joins Dave and Herb to talk shop on the 115th episode of Pensado's Place. The trio talk about Mick's recent mixing and tracking work on Daft Punk's "Random Access Memories" as well as his work on classic albums by Mariah Carey and Eric Clapton.

117.title: Al Schmitt
117.plot: 22-time GRAMMY winning Engineer and Producer Al Schmitt joins Dave and Herb.

118.title: Robert Duncan
118.plot: Two-time Emmy-award-nominated TV and Film composer (Buffy the Vampire Slayer, The Unit, Butterfly on a Wheel and Into the Blue 2: The Reef) Robert Duncan joins Dave and Herb.

119.title: Scotty McCreery
119.plot: Scotty McCreery, country music artist and winner of American Idol season 10 gives us a backstage pass to his recent "Weekend Roadtrip" tour.

120.title: Music Industry Question and Answer Session
120.plot: Dave and Herb host an in-depth industry Q&A Session.

imdb.plot outline: Top mixing engineer Dave Pensado talks all things music and audio in his weekly show, Pensado's Place. Dave gives you insights into his career and teaches you how to get that "platinum record" sound for your own mixes through tutorials and interviews.
imdb.title: Pensado's Place
plot: Top mixing engineer Dave Pensado talks all things music and audio in his weekly show, _Pensado's Place_ (qv). Dave gives you insights into his career and teaches you how to get that "platinum record" sound for your own mixes through tutorials and interviews.::Will Thompson
